            <thetext>As discussed in #8885 there are several documentation problems related to the qx.event.handler.GestureCore.TAP_MAX_DISTANCE constant:

1. The TAP_MAX_DISTANCE member of qx.event.handler.GestureCore class is mentioned in the API documentation (http://demo.qooxdoo.org/current/apiviewer/#qx.event.handler.GestureCore), but does not have any description.

2. The description text should mention that it is an array of integers, not a scalar value.

3. The API documentation lists this this member in the Constants section, however, according to Martin&#39;s comments in #8885, it is more like a global tunable, rather then a real constant (i.e. something that&#39;s not meant to be modified in run time). If TAP_MAX_DISTANCE is a tunable it should be clearly documented as such.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
